# Storage Engine (LSM-Tree)

## Write Path

```
Put(key, value)
  -> Append to WAL (sequential, fsync for durability)
  -> Insert into MemTable (sorted skip list)
  -> If MemTable full: flush to new SSTable, rotate WAL
```

## Read Path

```
Get(key)
  -> Check MemTable (newest data)
  -> Check immutable MemTables (being flushed)
  -> Check SSTables newest-first (use bloom filter to skip)
  -> Binary search index block within matching SSTable
```

## WAL Format

Binary, append-only: `[4-byte length][4-byte CRC32][1-byte type][key-len][val-len][key][value]`

- Types: Put=1, Delete=2
- `os.O_APPEND | os.O_WRONLY | os.O_CREATE` with `f.Sync()` after each write
- On recovery: replay WAL entries into fresh MemTable

## SSTable Format

```
[data block 0][data block 1]...[index block][bloom filter][footer]
- Data block: sorted key-value pairs, prefix-compressed
- Index block: [key, offset] pairs for binary search
- Bloom filter: probabilistic negative lookups
- Footer (fixed 16 bytes): index_offset(8) + bloom_offset(8)
```

Read strategy: seek to footer -> read index offset -> load index -> binary search.

## Compaction

- Size-tiered: when N SSTables exist at similar size, merge into one larger
- K-way merge: use heap/priority queue
- Tombstone processing: discard deleted keys during merge
- Run in background goroutine, never block writes

## Key Interfaces

```go
type Engine interface {
    Put(ctx context.Context, key, value []byte) error
    Get(ctx context.Context, key []byte) ([]byte, error)
    Delete(ctx context.Context, key []byte) error
    Scan(ctx context.Context, prefix []byte) Iterator
    Close() error
}
```
